<p class="EnTeteTranscription">Wentzel, Willard Ferdinand. A Continuation of the Journal of the Forks Mackenzie's River for Summer 1807-1808. An electronic transcription. MFTP #0022</p><div class="ContenuPage">
<p></p>
<p class="head">March Cont<sup>d</sup> 1808</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">led them to the Sea Shore where they comme<span class="AddHand-author">n</span>ced &#8211; this is wh<span class="DelHand-author">ich</span><span class="AddHand-author">at</span> the <span style="text-decoration:underline;">Gens</span> <span style="text-decoration:underline;">D'our</span> told the <span style="text-decoration:underline;">Gens</span> <span style="text-decoration:underline;">D'mouton</span><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  This is now the 11<sup>th</sup> day since Jollibois left the lodges &#8211; which Genereux tells me <span class="AddHand-author">may</span> be performed in 5 Days <span style="text-decoration:underline;">pars</span> <span style="text-decoration:underline;">des</span> <span style="text-decoration:underline;">gens</span> <span style="text-decoration:underline;">qui</span> <span style="text-decoration:underline;">voudra marcher</span><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Monday 29<sup>th</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Jollibois asked leave to remain a day or two here to mend his Cloaths &amp;<sup>c</sup> &amp;<sup>c</sup> to which I consented<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Sent Cadien to the Hare Hunter who came back with the latter &amp; 70 Hares<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  My Girl took a Lynx in <span style="text-decoration:underline;">Collets</span><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Thawed A little day<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Tues<sup>y</sup> 30<sup>th</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Sent one of the young <span class="AddHand-author">men</span> who came with Jollibois upon the Track of an Orignal &#8211; as I hope he will Kill it for he is reported to be a capital Butcher<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  In the afternoon he returned alledging that the Animal had been risen some time ago &#8211; &amp; that there was no crust upon the Snow to run him<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  However as the fellow seems willing to remain untill his father inlaw the Grand Chefre comes to the Fort I Keep him to Hunt hoping to detach him entirely from the lower quarter where nothing can be had<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Wednes<sup>y</sup> 31<sup>st</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Sent off <span style="text-decoration:underline;">Jollibois</span> to resume his Station w<sup>t</sup> Grand Chefre<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[G]</span>ave him all the instructions I could, upon what he Should do, to bring a Couple of the Strangers to the <span class="DelHand-author">Stranger</span> Fort<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[A]</span>t them same time sent word to the Grand Chefre to prevail upon them to come &amp; see me &#8211; that since they had no Beaver, that they might come with provisions &amp;<sup>c</sup> understanding that the animals were numerous thereabouts and that my directions might have the better effect upon the old Scoundral &#8211; I added 6 meas: Am: 1 P<sup>r</sup> Leggins &amp; 4 feet of Tobacco &#8211; but I excused myself with respect to the Gun<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Last night our House took Fire, which we however extinguished not without some difficulty, bei<span class="AddHand-author">n</span>g obliged to cut a great deal of Bark &amp;<sup>c</sup> away<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>

